"{\"abstract\":\"We present a wearable device able to perform online and long-term monitoring of ECG signals, and automatically detect anomalous heartbeats such as arrhythmias. The core of our solution are user-specific dictionaries, which are learned every time the device is positioned. Anomalies are detected via an optimized sparse coding procedure, which assesses the conformance of each heartbeat to the userspecific dictionary. User-specific dictionaries are adapted during online monitoring, to track heart rate variations occurring during everyday activities. Perhaps surprisingly, dictionary adaptation can be successfully performed by transformations that are user-independent and learned from large datasets of ECG signals.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2454401\",\"name\":\"M. Longoni\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2454401\"},{\"authorId\":\"145931074\",\"name\":\"D. Carrera\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/145931074\"},{\"authorId\":\"40191282\",\"name\":\"B. Rossi\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/40191282\"},{\"authorId\":\"2542454\",\"name\":\"P. Fragneto\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2542454\"},{\"authorId\":\"51055287\",\"name\":\"Marco Pessione\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/51055287\"},{\"authorId\":\"2772474\",\"name\":\"G. Boracchi\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2772474\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"145931074\",\"name\":\"D. Carrera\"},{\"authorId\":\"40191282\",\"name\":\"B. Rossi\"},{\"authorId\":\"2542454\",\"name\":\"P. Fragneto\"},{\"authorId\":\"2772474\",\"name\":\"G. Boracchi\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1016/j.patcog.2018.11.019\",\"intent\":[\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"235a7d58d1ac3f6f1446aec0f877f72fbf803390\",\"title\":\"Online anomaly detection for long-term ECG monitoring using wearable devices\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.or